\subsubsection{Hate Speech Analysis}

[领域简述]Hate speech analysis is a well-established field with a long history, yet its significance has been amplified in the modern social media era. In this digital landscape, users' real-world identities are often obscured, lowering the barrier for expressing harmful content and exacerbating real-world conflicts, such as 在covid-19疫情期间anti-Asian言论的大行其道\cite{budhwaniCreatingCOVID19Stigma2020,tesslerAnxietyBeingAsian2020,johnsonChinaVirusWent2020} and the Capitol Riots linked to fringe platforms \cite{kumarswamyCasualInsightsParlers2025}.当今社媒生活已经成为人类在现实生活之外另一个重要生活场景，因此寻找对hate speech进行有效管理的方式，从而让用户在更加健康和有秩序的社媒环境中浏览成为了一个重要课题\cite{shuklaSilencingEmpowermentAllowing2025,fieldPapers,sociologyPapers}. Hate speech analysis has traditionally been framed as a straightforward text classification task\cite{traditionMethodPapers}. However, this simplistic paradigm 常常不够适用 when confronting the real social media: hate is often implicit, multimodally disguised (e.g., memes), and subjective. The advent of Large Language Models (LLMs) has catalyzed a paradigm shift in this domain. We observe three emerging trends: 
\begin{itemize}
    \item From explicit to implicit: moving beyond keyword-based detection to understanding subtle, coded, and metaphorical expressions; \cite{typicalPapers}
    \item From unimodal to multimodal: 从单模态的仇恨文本检测发展到在多模态仇恨内容对齐的前提下进行仇恨检测;\cite{typicalPapers}
    \item From black-box to explainable: 从只需要输出标签的黑盒分类到生成与人类判断相符的解释性文本\cite{typicalPapers}
\end{itemize}从显式仇恨判别到隐式仇恨挖掘，从单模态仇恨文本内容检测到多模态仇恨内容对齐，从黑盒检测到可解释性检测的发展趋势，该领域的强文化依赖性促使越来越多的研究工作聚焦于low-resource and non-English languagesRecent efforts have actively built essential datasets and tailored models for diverse sociolinguistic contexts, ranging from Vietnamese \cite{thanhnguyenViHateT5EnhancingHate2024}, Arabic \cite{zaghouaniHatefulBuildingMultilabel2024}, Persian \cite{bokaeiCultureMattersToxic2025}, Polish\cite{kolosBANPLPolishDataset2024}, Korean\cite{parkKHATERSHateSpeech2023}, Portuguese\cite{sallesHateBRXplainBenchmarkDataset2025}, and Bengali\cite{dasBanglaAbuseMemeDatasetBengali2023,hossainDecipheringHateIdentifying2024}, to code-mixed languages or dialects in India\cite{kumariCMoffmemeCodemixedHindiEnglish2024} and  Singapore\cite{haberImprovingDetectionMultilingual2023}.[这个趋势长句可以作为面，每个给一些典型例子]

\paragraph{implicit and pragmatic hate detection}
[隐晦仇恨与语用性检测]As moderation systems become more adept at filtering explicit hate speech, malicious users 越来越多的使用implicit and coded language to evade detection. This pragmatic shift 对hate speech detector的语义理解能力提出了更高的要求.A typical example is "dogwhistles", 一种面向特定对象的编码修辞形式。它可以在公众面前表现地无害的同时，向特定群体传达有害信息. Mendelsohn et al. \cite{mendelsohnDogwhistlesBullhornsUnveiling2023} and Kruk et al. \cite{krukSilentSignalsLoud2024} 率先对其进行了 computational analyses 评估了LLMs处理such coded expression的能力，并构建了large-scale datasets. 此外，\cite{zengSheepsSkinWolfs2025} propose a jailbreaking and energy-based constrained decoding method to generate metaphorical implicit hate speech, revealing that state-of-the-art LLMs 普遍无法有效 detect such content. 以上研究highlight a 重要 vulnerability of LLMs in current moderation systems.
[语境融入很重要]To adress the semantic ambiguity of implicit hate, recent studies have advanced on two fronts. capturing 足够全面的 conversational context has proven essential\cite{bourgeadeHumansNeedContext2024}. Nouri et al. \cite{nouriGraphicallySpeakingUnmasking2025} 创新性地 utilized Graph Neural Networks (GNNs) to model the structural topology of comment threads, 节点表示评论，边表示回复结构, moving beyond naive text concatenation. CoSyn\cite{ghoshCoSynDetectingImplicit2023} integrated user and conversational contexts into a hyperbolic space, achieving performance improvements across six datasets for hate speech detection. Second, to prevent models from overfitting to 特定场景，更准确地识别隐式仇恨特征, researchers 使用了 contrastive learning methods. By introducing causality-guided sample alignment \cite{jiangLearnFailureCausalityguided2025} and label-aware hard negative sampling \cite{kimLabelawareHardNegative2024}, these methods significantly improve the cross-domain generalization of implicit hate detection.

\paragraph{Alignment challenges in multimodal hate detection}
[多模态仇恨检测的的对齐挑战（旧论文库上大分）]当前社媒平台上视觉内容，尤其是memes成为了一种主流传播媒介，The core challenge in multimodal hate detection is the "modality gap": hateful intent often emerges not from the isolated text or image, but from their non-literal association or semantic contradiction, such as a 无害的 image with a sarcastic caption. 这种隐含的恶意首先需要hate detection方法拥有足够的模态对齐能力. 

To bridge this semantic gap, recent advancements focus on fine-grained cross-modal alignment and contrastive learning. Zhang et al. 提出了基于Optimal Transport(OT)和topology-aware graph的TOT框架\cite{zhangTOTTopologyawareOptimal2023}，使用数学方法将CLIP生成的特征矩阵级别的对齐，细粒化为特征向量间的对齐，从而提升了multimodal hate detection, 随后进一步改进，引入了可学习的OT参数和对比图建模，提出了FLOT框架\cite{zhangFlexibleOptimalTransport2025}, 使对齐效果进一步提升。 为了捕捉这种跨模态语义联系，Mei et al. \cite{meiImprovingHatefulMeme2024a} 使用了另一种思路. They introduced a retrieval-guided contrastive learning approach to construct a hatefulness-aware embedding space. 采用动态检索挖掘困难样本从而更好地学习到 subtle visual-textual differences, outperforming much larger general-purpose multimodal models without requiring massive parameter updates. Beyond feature-level alignment, Kumari et al. \cite{kumariM3HopCoTMisogynousMeme2024} proposed M3Hop-CoT, 尝试利用multimodal multi-hop Chain-of-Thought prompting，引导大型语言模型识别emotions, target awareness, and contextual knowledge这三个关键线索, significantly improving the identification of subtle misogynous memes.
[AI生成,备用：此外，大量的研究也在探索多模态仇恨检测的其它边界，包括 addressing uncertainty in cross-modal alignment \cite{yangUncertaintyawareCrossmodalAlignment2024}, facilitating cross-modality knowledge transfer via few-shot in-context learning \cite{heeBridgingModalitiesEnhancing2024}, 以及将多模态对齐从孤立的meme扩展到包含整个Reddit讨论树上下文的 Graph Transformers 中 \cite{hebertMultimodalDiscussionTransformer2024}.]

