\subsubsection{Malicious user detection}
malicious user, 的 detection 对于社媒环境的环境净化和舆论管控有重要意义, 尤其是bot user，它常常作为舆论恶意引导者的botnet的组成部分。社交媒体上的这种恶意机器人（Bots）不仅是零星的存在，它们已经形成了极具规模的群体，并在重大社会政治事件（如马斯克推特投票、国家选举等）中占据了惊人的比例 \cite{tanBotPercentEstimatingBot2023}。因此，在LLM时代开发更强大的检测方法也愈发重要。Malicious user detectio tasks一般需要把握social content中subtle linguistic cues, or 特定的用户行为patterns, 从而识别出异常用户. Given the inherent network topology of social interactions,  Graph Neural Networks (GNNs) have largely superseded other early machine learning techniques by effectively capturing node topological information. Recent state-of-the-art GNN approaches have advanced to model highly complex community-aware heterogeneous structures \cite{chenCACLCommunityawareHeterogeneous2024} and dynamic temporal graphs \cite{heDynamicityawareSocialBot2024}. Furthermore, ，为了防止bots establish heterophilic connections with humans to evade detection through feature smoothing，一些study尝试建模异常用户与正常用户之间连接的异质性. For instance, Li et al. \cite{liMultimodalSocialBot2023} proposed BothH. They augment the retweet graph with node feature similarity edges, 连接起孤立的机器人节点，ensuring that bot features are not smoothed out by surrounding human nodes. On the highly heterophilic Twibot-20 benchmark, BothH achieves 91.27\% F1, 表现出state-of-the art性能. 不同于BothH对异质关系进行显性的建模，\cite{qiaoDispellingFakeSocial2025}选择剪除特征偏离正常分布的边来移除异常用户与正常用户之间的异质关系，以防止机器人的特征被正常用户平滑。

i单纯的GNN（图神经网络）方法善于抓取网络拓扑结构，相比之下LLM凭借强大的语义理解能力，能对用户生成内容（UGC）进行深度分析，从而在恶意用户（Bot）检测中展现出独特的优势。\cite{fengWhatDoesBot2024} revealed that instruction-tuned LLMs significantly outperform state-of-the-art GNN baselines by inherently capturing the pragmatic nuances within bot texts. To further leverage this semantic superiority, the ETS-MM framework \cite{liETSMMMultimodalSocial2025} 试图同时利用GNN的拓扑感知能力和LLM的语义理解能力. It utilizes LLMs to extract multi-dimensional semantic features, specifically topic preferences and emotion tendencies, from user's social contents, 使用GNN方法多轮聚合包含语义特征信息的节点特征，achieving state-of-the-art performance on benchmark datasets.
Furthermore, advanced semantic modeling capabilities 可以帮助模型真正的理解内容，从而更好地识别语义不一致问题。For instance, BIC\cite{leiBICTwitterBot2023} introduces a text-graph interaction module and a semantic consistency module to detect semantic consistency across a user's chronological posts. It 轻松识别出了那些试图通过窃取真实user推文来规避检测的机器人。这些研究表明，LLM在malicious user detection领域具有能够理解intention等深层语义信息的独特优势，因此使用LLM可以将检测范围 from mere network topology 扩展到deep semantic verification，从而获得更强大的malicious user 检测能力

